 rail\ngroup. Duquesne Light 4Vas, fraction\nally above par; Columbia Gas ss, Utah\nPower and Light 5s and International\nTelephone 5s (1955) were the most\npopular utility issues.\nThe convertible list was ragged, with\nadvances in Alleghany 5s <19501, New\nHaven 6s, American International 5 (is\nand Philadelphia Reading Coal\nIron 6s, and declines in American I. G.\nChemical s*\u00a3s, Chicago Northwestern\n4~\u00abs, Atchison 4\u2019is, Southern Pacific\n4 2\u00ae, American Telephone 4tss and\nTexas Corporation ss.\nSt. Paul adjustments, which have\nscored a 5-point, advance in the past 10\ndays; Frisco 4\u00bb 2 s, another large gainer,\nand Boston Maine ss. which has\nmoved upward about 3 points in the\nsame period, were active in the junior\nrail list. All were off fractionally. Good\nyear ss. United States Rubber ss,\nDodge 6s and Anglo-Chilean Nitrate\n7s suffered from profit taking. There\nwas 2-point advance in Certainteed\n5'' 2 s and one of 3Mi points In Colon\nOil 6s.\nWashington Stock Exchange\nSALES.\nMergenthaler Linotype\u20144 at 108*4, 6\nat 106 3 '4, 10 at 106*4, 10 at 106*i, 10\nat 106 7 5 at 107, 5 at 107.\nPeoples Drug Stores pfd\u2014s at 105*4, 5\nat 105*4, 10 at 105>i, 10 at 105%.\nReal Estate Mtge. <fc Guar, pfd.\u2014Bo at 7.\nSecurity Storage Co.\u2014lo at 115.\nThe Carpel Corp.\u2014ss at 25.\nAFTER CALL.\nWashington Rwy. Electric 4s\u2014sl,ooo\nat 87, SI,OOO at 87.\nPotomac Electric 5*4% pfd.\u2014l7 at\n108*4.\nRiggs National Bank\u20146 at 525.\nPotomac Electric 6% pfd.\u20142 at 111%.\nNotice\u2014This exchange will convene\non Monday next. March 24, at 11\no\u2019clock instead of 11:15. On Tuesday,\nMarch 25, it will meet in Room 632,\nWashington Building, the new location.\nBid and Asked Prices.\nBONDS.\nPUBLIC UTILITY.\nAmir Tel. Si Tele*. 4%* \u201953... ?00'i\nAmer Tel. A Telge. 4%e '69... 167\nAm. Tel. Tel ctl. tr. 6a 104'i\nAnacoatia Sc Pot. R. R. 5s 83 65\nAnacoatia As Pot. euar. 5a 93\nC. Sc P. Tel. of Va. 5a 100\nCapital